{"entries":[{"id":"tsk-mat-6-4","title":"Matthew 6:4","author":"R. A. Torrey (editor)","reference":{"book":"MAT","chapterStart":6,"verseStart":4,"chapterEnd":6,"verseEnd":4},"content":"<p>no. 11,25; Ex 16:18-20; La 3:23 for. De 33:25; 1Ki 17:4-6,14-16; 2Ki 7:1,2; Lu 11:3; Heb 13:5,6 Sufficient. Joh 14:27; 16:33; Ac 14:22; 1Th 3:3,4</p>"},{"id":"tsk-mat-6-9","title":"Matthew 6:9","author":"R. A. Torrey (editor)","reference":{"book":"MAT","chapterStart":6,"verseStart":9,"chapterEnd":6,"verseEnd":9},"content":"<p>Thou hypocrite. 22:18; 23:14-28; Lu 12:56; 13:15 first. Ps 51:9-13; Lu 4:23; 6:42; Ac 19:15</p>"},{"id":"tsk-mat-6-14","title":"Matthew 6:14","author":"R. A. Torrey (editor)","reference":{"book":"MAT","chapterStart":6,"verseStart":14,"chapterEnd":6,"verseEnd":14},"content":"<p>being. Ge 6:5; 8:21; Job 15:16; Jer 17:9; Ro 3:9,19; Ga 3:22; Eph 2:1-3 Tit 3:3 how. Ex 34:6,7; 2Sa 7:19; Ps 86:5,15; 103:11-13; Isa 49:15; 55:8,9 Ho 11:8,9; Mic 7:18; Mal 1:6; Lu 11:11-13; Joh 3:16; Ro 5:8-10; 8:32 Eph 2:4,5; 1Jo 3:1; 4:10 good. Ps 84:11; 85:12; Jer 33:14; Ho 14:2; *marg: Lu 2:10,11; 11:13; 2Co 9:8-15; Tit 3:4-7</p>"},{"id":"tsk-mat-6-19","title":"Matthew 6:19","author":"R. A. Torrey (editor)","reference":{"book":"MAT","chapterStart":6,"verseStart":19,"chapterEnd":6,"verseEnd":19},"content":"<p>every. Ps 1:3; 92:13,14; Isa 5:3-5; 61:3; Jer 11:19; 17:8; Lu 13:6-9 Ga 5:22-24; Eph 5:9; Php 1:11; Col 1:10; Jas 3:17,18 but. 12:33-35; Jude 1:12</p>"},{"id":"tsk-mat-6-24","title":"Matthew 6:24","author":"R. A. Torrey (editor)","reference":{"book":"MAT","chapterStart":6,"verseStart":24,"chapterEnd":6,"verseEnd":24},"content":"<p>I never. 25:12; Joh 10:14,27-30; 2Ti 2:19 depart. 25:41; Ps 5:5; 6:8; Lu 13:25,27; Re 22:15</p>"},{"id":"tsk-mat-6-29","title":"Matthew 6:29","author":"R. A. Torrey (editor)","reference":{"book":"MAT","chapterStart":6,"verseStart":29,"chapterEnd":6,"verseEnd":29},"content":"<p>having. 5:20,28,32,44; 21:23-27; 28:18; De 18:18,19; Ec 8:4; Isa 50:4 Jer 23:28,29; Mic 3:8; Lu 21:15; Ac 3:22,23; 6:10; Heb 4:12,13 and not. 15:1-9; 23:2-6,15-24; Mr 7:5-13; Lu 20:8,46,47</p>"},{"id":"tsk-mat-6-34","title":"Matthew 6:34","author":"R. A. Torrey (editor)","reference":{"book":"MAT","chapterStart":6,"verseStart":34,"chapterEnd":6,"verseEnd":34},"content":"<p>entered. 4:13; 9:1; 11:23; Mr 2:1; Lu 7:1 a centurion.This was a Roman military title; and therefore this officer may be concluded to have been a Gentile. (See fuller particulars under Mark 15:39.)</p>\n<p>27:54; Mr 15:39; Lu 7:2-10; Ac 10:1-33; 22:25; 23:17,23; 27:13,31,43</p>"}]}